The White House is hosting an event called South by South Lawn (SXSL) that celebrates innovation, art, and action. The event is a call to action for Americans to make a positive difference in the country. It will feature artists, creators, entrepreneurs, and innovators who have used their skills to create change in their communities. The event will include various activities such as art installations, virtual reality exhibits, and panel discussions on topics like technology, sustainability, and citizen engagement. President Obama will also participate in conversations with climate scientist Dr. Katherine Hayhoe and actor Leonardo DiCaprio about climate change. The event schedule includes musical performances and film screenings as well. The festival will be live-streamed on WhiteHouse.gov, Facebook, and sxsw.com.